<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="complain-v">complain <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /kəm'pleɪn/    美 /kəm'pleɪn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[不用于被动语态] 抱怨：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>“I didn't like that meal at all,” complained the customer.
顾客抱怨说：“我一点儿也不喜欢那饭菜。”</p></div>

<ul>
<li>complain (to sb) about / of:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ve really got nothing to complain of. 
我确实没什么可抱怨的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Young people now don’t look for jobs, but just complain about unemployment. 
现在的年轻人不去找工作，就会一味地抱怨失业。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We should strictly follow traffic rules rather than complain about traffic jams.
我们应该严格遵守交通规则，而不是抱怨交通堵塞。</p><footer>2013 江苏书面表达改</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>complain (to sb) + (that) 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Betty complained to Steve that Sara never gave her a chance to talk. 
贝蒂向史蒂夫抱怨说萨拉从不给她说话的机会。</p><footer>2010 北京</footer></div></div>